---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ScrollToTop from "../components/ScrollToTop.astro";

const title = "AI Stats Privacy Policy | Model Data Dashboard";
const description =
  "Privacy policy for AI Stats, including how model pricing data, benchmark data, public source links, and basic site interactions are handled.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <Header currentPage="privacy" />
  <main class="mx-auto min-h-[calc(100vh-7rem)] w-full max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-foam">Privacy policy</p>
    <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-4xl text-4xl font-black leading-tight text-text md:text-6xl">
      AI Stats publishes public model data for comparison.
    </h1>
    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-highlight-med bg-surface p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-text">Data sources</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-subtle">
          The dashboard displays public model pricing, benchmark, speed, context, and routing metadata from third-party sources.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-subtle">
          Source data is used to render model comparison pages and does not include private user records. Public provider names, model names, pricing fields, context sizes, speed metrics, and benchmark values are treated as reference data for browsing and comparison.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-highlight-med bg-surface p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-text">User accounts</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-subtle">
          AI Stats does not require account creation, login, or payment information to browse comparison pages.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-subtle">
          The site is designed as a public reference dashboard. It does not ask visitors to submit passwords, payment details, API keys, or private model usage data in order to compare models.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-highlight-med bg-surface p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-text">Questions</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-subtle">
          Privacy questions and correction requests can be sent through Jonathan Reed's portfolio contact channels.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-subtle">
          Requests should identify the relevant AI Stats page and the concern being raised, such as a data correction, source attribution question, accessibility issue, or privacy question about how the site presents public model data.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="rounded-lg border border-highlight-med bg-surface p-6 md:col-span-3">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-text">Site behavior</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-subtle">
          AI Stats may use normal browser behavior such as theme preferences and client-side filtering to make the dashboard easier to use. These interactions are intended to improve comparison workflows and are not required to create a visitor account or profile.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-subtle">
          External source links may lead to third-party sites with their own privacy practices. Review those policies when leaving AI Stats for provider documentation, benchmark publishers, or model routing catalogs.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
  <ScrollToTop />
</Layout>
